Scene 2 — Victim vs cause trap
Image prompt

Residential street. A house is on fire (visible flames). A person is lying on the ground nearby (not injured, not burning). A car is parked close to the house. Daytime.

Caption

“A house is burning while a person lies nearby, and a car is parked close to the house.”

Objects present (intended)

house, fire, person, car, street

What it tests

Cause vs victim discrimination

Whether the model incorrectly treats a salient person as a cause

Suppression selection correctness

Expected causal behavior

Suppression variable: fire / burning house

PAG: fire/house → HazardLevel → recommendations

Person should not be a causal driver of hazard (at most a protection target)

CEE failure modes exposed

Structural error (person → HazardLevel edges)

Behavioral Mimicry (behavior shifts without correct hazard→action structure)

Semantic Illusion (fluent explanation justifying wrong causal role)

Wrong suppression type (person chosen)